    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your<strong> potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into thin chips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 12-15 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>truffle oil </strong>in a bowl with a splash of <strong>water </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Add 1/4 of your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>truffle mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chips have had an initial 12 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add your<strong> meat-free patty[ies]</strong> to piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> on the tray[s] and pull up the edges of the foil to form an open parcel</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven and cook for 10-12 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>Once everything is nearly ready, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>brioche halves</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-truffled-plant-based-burger-with-sweet-potato-chips/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, put a handful of <strong>salad</strong> on the<strong> brioche bun base</strong>, top with a <strong>meat-free patty </strong>and spread over a generous dollop of the <strong>truffle mayo </strong>and <strong>onion marmalade</strong>, then<strong> </strong>top with the <strong>brioche lid</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>remaining salad </strong>and <strong>chopped tomato </strong>to the side and dress with the <strong>remaining cider vinegar</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, serve the <strong>chips</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
